  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `Geth/v1.6.5-stable-cf87713d/darwin-amd64/go1.8.3`\r\nOS & Version: OSX\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nTo get the number of transactions as [per documentation](https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/blob/master/JSON-RPC.md#eth_getblocktransactioncountbyhash)\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nI am getting `null` instead of a hexadecimal string for the `result`:\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n```\r\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8545 --data '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"eth_getBlockTransactionCountByHash\",\"params\":[\"0xb903239f8543d04b5dc1ba6579132b143087c68db1b2168786408fcbce568238\"],\"id\":1}' \r\n```\r\nproduces:\r\n\r\n```\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"result\":null}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI also tried with the infura.io service and got the exact same result.\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\nN/A",
